My Friend Leonard is a memoir written by James Frey. Continuing where A Million Little Pieces left off, the book centers on the father-son relationship Frey and his friend from Hazelden, Leonard, shared. My Friend Leonard was published in June 2005 by Riverhead, and became a bestseller. Amazon.com editors selected My Friend Leonard as their #5 favorite book of 2005. The book was marketed as a memoir, but after its release, certain elements of the story were cast into doubt. The author later admitted that he had never actually been incarcerated as claimed in the book.